#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta author="Bhikkhu Brahmali"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="en"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Bhedā­nu­vatta­ka­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "11. The training rule on supporting a schism"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.175"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.304"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.11.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1704"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalanda­ka­nivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena devadatto saṃghabhedāya parakkamati cakkabhedāya."
msgstr ""
"At that time Devadatta was pursuing schism in the Order, a break in "
"transmission."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The monks were saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "“adhammavādī devadatto, avinayavādī devadatto."
msgstr ""
"“Devadatta doesn’t speak in accordance with the Teaching or the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma devadatto saṃghabhedāya parakkamissati cakkabhedāyā”ti."
msgstr "How can he pursue schism in the Order?”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: kokāliko → kokāliko ca (bj)
#. VAR: samuddadatto → samuddadatto ca (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, kokāliko kaṭa­modaka­tissako khaṇḍadeviyā putto samuddadatto te "
"bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"But Kokālika, Kaṭamodakatissaka, Khaṇḍadeviyā-putta, and Samuddadatta said "
"to those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“māyasmanto evaṃ avacuttha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t say that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Dhammavādī devadatto, vinayavādī devadatto."
msgstr "Devadatta does speak in accordance with the Teaching and the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"Amhākañca devadatto chandañca ruciñca ādāya voharati jānāti no bhāsati "
"amhākampetaṃ khamatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And he speaks with our consent and approval. He knows about us and speaks "
"for us, and we agree to this.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū devadattassa saṃghabhedāya parakka­man­tassa "
"anuvattakā bhavissanti vaggavādakā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can these monks support Devadatta’s pursuit of schism in the Order?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1705"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū te anuvattake bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They rebuked those monks in many ways and then told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.14"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū devadattassa saṃghabhedāya parakka­man­"
"tassa anuvattakā honti vaggavādakā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"He said, “Is it true, monks, that some monks support Devadatta’s pursuit of "
"schism in the Order?”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.305"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā devadattassa saṃghabhedāya "
"parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā bhavissanti vaggavādakā."
msgstr ""
"Monks, how can those foolish men support Devadatta’s pursuit of schism in "
"the Order?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1706"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.20"
msgid ""
"“Tasseva kho pana bhikkhussa bhikkhū honti anuvattakā vaggavādakā eko vā dve "
"vā tayo vā."
msgstr ""
"‘That monk may have one, two, or three monks who take his side and support "
"him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "Te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ—"
msgstr "and they may say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "‘māyasmanto etaṃ bhikkhuṃ kiñci avacuttha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t correct this monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "Dhammavādī ceso bhikkhu, vinayavādī ceso bhikkhu."
msgstr "He speaks in accordance with the Teaching and the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"Amhākañceso bhikkhu chandañca ruciñca ādāya voharati jānāti no bhāsati "
"amhākampetaṃ khamatī’ti,"
msgstr ""
"And he speaks with our consent and approval. He knows about us and speaks "
"for us, and we agree to this.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "te bhikkhū bhikkhūhi evamassu vacanīyā—"
msgstr "The monks should say to those monks,"

#. VAR: māyasmanto → mā āyasmanto (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "‘māyasmanto evaṃ avacuttha,"
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t say that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.27"
msgid "na ceso bhikkhu dhammavādī, na ceso bhikkhu vinayavādī,"
msgstr ""
"This monk does not speak in accordance with the Teaching or the training."

#. VAR: mā­yasman­tānampi → mā āyasmantānampi (bj, s1-3) | māyasmantānaṃ pi (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "­mā­yasman­tānampi saṃghabhedo ruccittha,"
msgstr "Don’t consent to schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "­same­tā­yasman­tānaṃ saṃghena,"
msgstr "Stay with the Order,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "­samaggo hi saṃgho sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsu viharatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"for a united Order—in concord, in harmony, having a joint recitation—lives "
"in comfort.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.31"
msgid ""
"Evañca te bhikkhū bhikkhūhi vuccamānā tatheva paggaṇheyyuṃ, te bhikkhū "
"bhikkhūhi yāvatatiyaṃ sama­nubhā­si­tabbā tassa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr ""
"If those monks still continue as before, the monks should admonish them up "
"to three times to make them stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.32"
msgid ""
"Yāvatatiyañce sama­nubhā­si­yamānā taṃ paṭi­nissaj­jey­yuṃ, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ,"
msgstr "If they then stop, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "no ce paṭi­nissaj­jey­yuṃ, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "If not, they commit an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs1.34"
msgid "(<em>11</em>:<strong>15</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.11.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1707"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tasseva kho panāti"
msgstr "That:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "tassa saṃgha­bheda­kassa bhikkhuno."
msgstr "that monk who is pursuing schism in the Order."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1708"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū hontīti"
msgstr "May have […] monks:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "aññe bhikkhū honti."
msgstr "may have other monks."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1709"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Anuvattakāti"
msgstr "Who take his side:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.6"
msgid ""
"yaṃdiṭṭhiko so hoti yaṃkhantiko yaṃruciko tepi taṃdiṭṭhikā honti taṃkhantikā "
"taṃrucikā."
msgstr ""
"they have the same view, the same belief, the same persuasion as he does."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1710"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Vaggavādakāti"
msgstr "Who […] support him:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "tassa vaṇṇāya pakkhāya ṭhitā honti."
msgstr "they take his side and are part of his group."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.176"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.306"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1711"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Eko vā dve vā tayo vāti"
msgstr "One, two, or three:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "eko vā hoti dve vā tayo vā."
msgstr "There is one, or two, or three."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ—"
msgstr "They may say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "“māyasmanto etaṃ bhikkhuṃ kiñci avacuttha,"
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t correct this monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "dhammavādī ceso bhikkhu, vinayavādī ceso bhikkhu,"
msgstr "He speaks in accordance with the Teaching and the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.14"
msgid ""
"amhākañceso bhikkhu chandañca ruciñca ādāya voharati jānāti no bhāsati "
"amhākampetaṃ khamatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And he speaks with our consent and approval. He knows about us and speaks "
"for us, and we agree to this.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1712"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Te bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Those monks:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "ye te anuvattakā bhikkhū."
msgstr "those monks who take his side."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1713"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "Bhikkhūhīti"
msgstr "The monks:"

#. </span>
#. </p><div class="gloss"><p><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1714"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "aññehi bhikkhūhi."
msgstr "Other monks,"

#. <a class="sc" id="11"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "Ye passanti ye suṇanti tehi vattabbā—"
msgstr "those who see it or hear about it. They should say,"

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "“māyasmanto evaṃ avacuttha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t say that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "Na ceso bhikkhu dhammavādī, na ceso bhikkhu vinayavādī."
msgstr ""
"This monk does not speak in accordance with the Teaching or the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "­Mā­yasman­tānampi saṃghabhedo ruccittha."
msgstr "Don’t consent to schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "Same­tā­yasman­tānaṃ saṃghena."
msgstr "Stay with the Order,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Samaggo hi saṃgho sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsu viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"for a united Order—in concord, in harmony, having a joint recitation—lives "
"in comfort.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbā."
msgstr "And they should say this a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "Sace paṭi­nissaj­janti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If they stop, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "no ce paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If they do not stop, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <span class="subrule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If those who hear about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

#. </span>
#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "Te bhikkhū saṃgha­majjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbā—"
msgstr ""
"Those monks, even if they have to be dragged into the middle of the Order, "
"should be to spoken to thus:"

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "“māyasmanto evaṃ avacuttha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t say that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "Na ceso bhikkhu dhammavādī, na ceso bhikkhu vinayavādī."
msgstr ""
"This monk does not speak in accordance with the Teaching or the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "­Mā­yasman­tānampi saṃghabhedo ruccittha."
msgstr "Don’t consent to schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "Same­tā­yasman­tānaṃ saṃghena."
msgstr "Stay with the Order,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "Samaggo hi saṃgho sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsu viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"for a united Order—in concord, in harmony, having a joint recitation—lives "
"in comfort.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.36"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbā."
msgstr "They should say this a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.38"
msgid "Sace paṭi­nissaj­janti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If they stop, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.39"
msgid "no ce paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If they do not stop, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p></div><p>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.40"
msgid "Te bhikkhū sama­nubhā­si­tabbā."
msgstr "Should admonish them:"

#. </span>
#. </p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.41"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sama­nubhā­si­tabbā."
msgstr "“And, monks, they should be admonished in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.42"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1715"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.43"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.44"
msgid ""
"Itthannāmo ca itthanāmo ca bhikkhū itthannāmassa bhikkhuno saṃghabhedāya "
"parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā vaggavādakā."
msgstr ""
"Monks so-and-so and so-and-so are taking sides with and supporting monk so-"
"and-so who is pursuing schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.45"
msgid "Te taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭi­nissaj­janti."
msgstr "They are not stopping that activity."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.46"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū "
"samanubhāseyya tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should admonish them to make "
"them stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.47"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1716"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.48"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.49"
msgid ""
"Itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhū itthannāmassa bhikkhuno saṃghabhedāya "
"parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā vaggavādakā."
msgstr ""
"Monks so-and-so and so-and-so are taking sides with and supporting monk so-"
"and-so who is pursuing schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.50"
msgid "Te taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭi­nissaj­janti."
msgstr "They are not stopping that activity."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.51"
msgid ""
"Saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa "
"paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "The Order admonishes them to make them stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.52"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa ca itthannāmassa ca bhikkhūnaṃ "
"samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of admonishing them to make them stop should remain "
"silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.53"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1717"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.54"
msgid "Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi … pe …"
msgstr "A second time …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.55"
msgid "tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "A third time I speak on this matter:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.56"
msgid "suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.57"
msgid ""
"Itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhū itthannāmassa bhikkhuno saṃghabhedāya "
"parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā vaggavādakā."
msgstr ""
"Monks so-and-so and so-and-so are taking sides with and supporting monk so-"
"and-so who is pursuing schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.58"
msgid "Te taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭi­nissaj­janti."
msgstr "They are not stopping that activity."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.59"
msgid ""
"Saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa "
"paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "The Order admonishes them to make them stop."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.307"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.60"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa ca itthannāmassa ca bhikkhūnaṃ "
"samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of admonishing them to make them stop should remain "
"silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.61"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1718"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.62"
msgid ""
"Samanubhaṭṭhā saṃghena itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhū tassa vatthussa "
"paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr ""
"The monks so-and-so and so-and-so have been admonished by the Order to make "
"them stop that activity."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.63"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.64"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></div></div><hr><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1719"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.65"
msgid "Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ,"
msgstr "After the motion, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.66"
msgid "dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā,"
msgstr ""
"After each of the first two announcements, they commit a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.67"
msgid "kamma­vācā­pari­yosāne āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"When the last announcement is finished, they commit an offense entailing "
"suspension."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.68"
msgid ""
"Saṃghādisesaṃ ajjhā­pajjan­tānaṃ ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ, dvīhi kammavācāhi "
"thullaccayā paṭippas­sam­bhanti."
msgstr ""
"For those who commit the offense entailing suspension, the offense of wrong "
"conduct and the serious offenses are annulled."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.69"
msgid "Dve tayo ekato sama­nubhā­si­tabbā, taduttari na sama­nubhā­si­tabbā."
msgstr "Two or three can be admonished together, but not more than that."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1720"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.70"
msgid "Saṃghādisesoti"
msgstr "They commit an offense entailing suspension:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs2.71"
msgid "… pe … tenapi vuccati “saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "… Therefore, too, it is called “an offense entailing suspension.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.177"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.11.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.11.3.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1721"></a> 
#. VAR: dhamma­kamma­saññī → dhamma­kamma­saññino (si)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammakamme dhamma­kamma­saññī na paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti "
"saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, and they perceive it as legitimate, but "
"they do not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1722"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "Dhammakamme vematikā na paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but they are unsure if it is, and they do "
"not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1723"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid ""
"Dhammakamme adhamma­kamma­saññī na paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti "
"saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but they perceive it as illegitimate, and "
"they do not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1724"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "Adhammakamme dhamma­kamma­saññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but they perceive it as legitimate, they "
"commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1725"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but they are unsure if it is, they "
"commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1726"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Adhammakamme adhamma­kamma­saññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, and they perceive it as illegitimate, "
"they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.11.3.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.308"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1727"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid "asama­nu­bhāsan­tā­naṃ,"
msgstr "if they have not been admonished;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid "paṭi­nissaj­jan­tānaṃ,"
msgstr "if they stop;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "ummattakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if they are insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "khittacittānaṃ,"
msgstr "if they are deranged;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "vedanāṭṭānaṃ,"
msgstr "if they are overwhelmed by pain;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid "ādi­kammi­kā­nanti."
msgstr "if they are the first offenders."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1728"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:pts-cs3.2.8"
msgid "Bhedā­nu­vatta­ka­sikkhā­padaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The eleventh rule, the training rule on supporting a schism, is finished."

